Recommended workflow for the user
The intended usage flow is:

Remove the 940nm bandpass filter temporarily
Turn on Live View — the camera will run continuous AF (AfMode=2) since ManualFocusEnable is still False
Wait a few seconds for AF to settle on the petri plate in position 1
Open Camera Config (Live View stays running in the background)
Press "Read Current Position from Camera" — the spinbox populates with the measured value (should be ~7.5 diopters) and the hint label shows the equivalent distance in cm as a sanity check
Check "Use manual focus"
Press Apply — this immediately calls set_manual_focus() so you can verify sharpness in the live view before closing
Press Close
Replace the bandpass filter
Verify the live view is still sharp — it should be, since the lens position is now pinned and start_camera() will restore it on every subsequent pipeline restart